lass=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 13, 2022</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bns1665702777767.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bns1665702777767.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bns1665702777767.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bns1665702777767\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      SQL Support on ODBC\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"bns1665702777767__sql_support_on_odbc_163477\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bns1665702777767__p_d54965e1_d54966e1_d54967e1\">Both the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor are supported.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bns1665702777767__topic_d36337e1_d36338e1_d36339e1_d36340e1_d36341e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1212677e62\">\n                        \n Allowed Commands\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bns1665702777767__p_d54971e1_d54972e1_d54973e1\">For a complete list of SQL commands that can be executed within a user transaction, see your DBMS documentation. The network protocol you use might influence the type of commands that you are allowed to issue.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bns1665702777767__topic_d36342e1_d36343e1_d36344e1_d36345e1_d36346e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1212677e71\">\n                        \n Transaction Control\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bns1665702777767__p_d54977e1_d54978e1_d54979e1\">Supported when the DBMS used supports it. The commands that involve transaction management are:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bns1665702777767__li_d25319e1_d25320e1_d25321e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">commit</span> (ProcScript command)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bns1665702777767__li_d25322e1_d25323e1_d25324e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">rollback</span> (ProcScript command)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bns1665702777767__li_d25325e1_d25326e1_d25327e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">commit transaction</code> (depending on the DBMS)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bns1665702777767__li_d25328e1_d25329e1_d25330e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">rollback transaction</code> (depending on the DBMS)\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"bns1665702777767__li_d25331e1_d25332e1_d25333e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">begin transaction</code> (depending on the DBMS)\n </li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If you perform transaction management, once the transaction finishes, you must ensure that the logon path is returned to the same state as it was before the transaction management was performed. If you do not do this, the ODBC Connector does not understand the correct state of the connection.</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bns1665702777767__topic_d36347e1_d36348e1_d36349e1_d36350e1_d36351e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1212677e116\">\n                        \n Monitoring SQL in the Message Frame\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bns1665702777767__p_d54983e1_d54984e1_d54985e1\">If requested in the application shell, the SQL generated by Uniface can be sent to the message frame. Error messages from ODBC are always sent to the message frame. The SQL statements in the message frame do not display values for inserts and updates since the parameters are bound by the Connector.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bns1665702777767__p_d54986e1_d54987e1_d54988e1\">To receive all ODBC information messages and the results in the message frame, set the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/pri</span> command line switch to 32 or higher.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526148\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526148\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "SQL Support on ODBC Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 13, 2022 Summarize Uniface 10.4 SQL Support on ODBC Both the sql ProcScript instruction and SQL Editor are supported. Allowed Commands For a complete list of SQL commands that can be executed within a user transaction, see your DBMS documentation. The network protocol you use might influence the type of commands that you are allowed to issue. Transaction Control Supported when the DBMS used supports it. The commands that involve transaction management are: commit (ProcScript command) rollback (ProcScript command) commit transaction (depending on the DBMS) rollback transaction (depending on the DBMS) begin transaction (depending on the DBMS) Note: If you perform transaction management, once the transaction finishes, you must ensure that the logon path is returned to the same state as it was before the transaction management was performed. If you do not do this, the ODBC Connector does not understand the correct state of the connection. Monitoring SQL in the Message Frame If requested in the application shell, the SQL generated by Uniface can be sent to the message frame. Error messages from ODBC are always sent to the message frame. The SQL statements in the message frame do not display values for inserts and updates since the parameters are bound by the Connector. To receive all ODBC information messages and the results in the message frame, set the /pri command line switch to 32 or higher. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}